#: ../../../faq.rst:271
msgid "What's the best way to parse big XML/CSV data feeds?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../faq.rst:273
msgid ""
"Parsing big feeds with XPath selectors can be problematic since they need to "
"build the DOM of the entire feed in memory, and this can be quite slow and "
"consume a lot of memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../faq.rst:277
msgid ""
"In order to avoid parsing all the entire feed at once in memory, you can use "
"the :func:`~scrapy.utils.iterators.xmliter_lxml` and :func:`~scrapy.utils."
"iterators.csviter` functions. In fact, this is what :class:`~scrapy.spiders."
"XMLFeedSpider` uses."
msgstr ""

